00:30:50,586 --> 00:30:54,796
And those are our
changes to My Apps.


604
00:30:54,916 --> 00:30:59,686
I want to talk about
users and roles,


605
00:31:00,566 --> 00:31:03,076
and there's three new features
we are going to be introducing.


606
00:31:03,216 --> 00:31:06,526
The first is account switching,
the ability to use one user name


607
00:31:06,526 --> 00:31:08,176
to log into multiple accounts.


608
00:31:09,476 --> 00:31:12,086
[ Applause ]


609
00:31:12,586 --> 00:31:14,976
The second is app siloing,
where you can separate


610
00:31:14,976 --> 00:31:16,706
which apps different
users can see.


611
00:31:18,016 --> 00:31:20,216
[ Applause ]


612
00:31:20,716 --> 00:31:22,346
And the third are some
new users and roles


613
00:31:22,346 --> 00:31:23,636
to help with these features.


614
00:31:24,146 --> 00:31:26,256
Let's start with
account switching.


615
00:31:27,206 --> 00:31:29,126
As you log in, you
have your user name,


616
00:31:29,126 --> 00:31:31,656
you log into your account,
and as you get access to more


617
00:31:31,656 --> 00:31:34,966
and more accounts, you create
new user names for each account.


618
00:31:36,156 --> 00:31:37,916
With account switching,
you'll be able


619
00:31:37,916 --> 00:31:39,686
to use a single user name to log


620
00:31:39,686 --> 00:31:41,616
into all these different
accounts.


621
00:31:42,836 --> 00:31:45,226
But with each account, you have
different apps that you see,


622
00:31:45,226 --> 00:31:46,236
you have different roles.


623
00:31:46,236 --> 00:31:50,456
So we will make it so that as
you log in and you can switch


624
00:31:51,276 --> 00:31:53,516
which account that
you want to view,


625
00:31:54,456 --> 00:31:56,146
will change those
apps that you see.


626
00:31:56,506 --> 00:31:59,076
You will get those roles and
permissions that you have


627
00:31:59,126 --> 00:32:00,946
for the account that
you've now moved to.


628
00:32:02,156 --> 00:32:02,986
And that's account switching.


629
00:32:03,486 --> 00:32:10,456
Every account starts with
one user, your admin user.


630
00:32:11,476 --> 00:32:16,696
As you start adding more and
more apps to this account,


631
00:32:17,246 --> 00:32:19,456
you start adding
more and more users.


632
00:32:20,866 --> 00:32:22,646
Most of these users
are technical users,


633
00:32:23,386 --> 00:32:26,946
but what you found is you want
some users to see some apps


634
00:32:27,516 --> 00:32:29,086
and some users to
see other apps.


635
00:32:29,086 --> 00:32:32,636
So what we are going to do is
we are going to separate this


636
00:32:33,246 --> 00:32:34,886
into three different areas.


637
00:32:37,256 --> 00:32:39,836
We also realize that Technical
User is a little bit broad,


638
00:32:40,196 --> 00:32:41,726
so we are going to
deprecate Technical


639
00:32:42,066 --> 00:32:44,216
with a new role called
App Manager.


640
00:32:45,066 --> 00:32:47,836
This App Manager will be
able to manage these apps


641
00:32:49,006 --> 00:32:49,946
in iTunes Connect for you.


642
00:32:50,026 --> 00:32:54,046
We are going to add two new
roles, Developer and Marketer,


643
00:32:54,046 --> 00:32:55,406
to help out with this.


644
00:32:55,656 --> 00:32:57,146
Let's talk about what
these roles entail.


645
00:32:57,756 --> 00:33:01,706
In App Manager, they will
be able to create users,


646
00:33:01,796 --> 00:33:07,546
change pricing, invite new
people to these different roles


647
00:33:07,546 --> 00:33:09,976
that we have, as well as
submit apps for review,


648
00:33:09,976 --> 00:33:14,246
both beta and for App Store.


649
00:33:14,456 --> 00:33:17,106
The Developer role will be able
to do developer kinds of things,


650
00:33:17,346 --> 00:33:19,686
upload the binaries,
view the crash logs,


651
00:33:20,106 --> 00:33:23,266
and view the store
metadata in iTunes Connect.


